Without warning
as a whirlwind
swoops on an oak
Love shakes my heart

-- Sappho.

Telling me you're not good enough.

My life with you is just too tough.

You know it's not right so.

Just stop and come back boy.

How can this be when we were meant to be...

 

 

 

(READY...)

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

I want nobody nobody But You

I want nobody nobody But You.

How can I be with another, I don't want any other

I want nobody nobody nobody nobody...

Clearly, this is my favorite part. As what my sophomore high school English teacher have said, every time you re-read The Little Prince, it speaks to you differently. It is good to be reminded by the fox, the rose, and the little prince. =)

****************************************

"Come and play with me, I am so unhappy."

"I cannot play with you,"I am not tamed."

"Ah! Please excuse me, what does that mean - 'tame'?"

"It means to establish ties."

"'To establish ties'?"

"Just that, to me, you are still nothing more than a little boy who is just like a hundred thousand other little boys. And I have no need of you. And you, on your part, have no need of me. To you, I am nothing more than a fox like a hundred thousand other foxes. But if you tame me, then we shall need each other. To me, you will be unique in all the world. To you, I shall be unique in all the world..."

"I am beginning to understand, there is a flower...I think that she has tamed me..."

"It is possible, on the Earth one sees all sorts of things."

"Oh, but this is not on the Earth!"

"On another planet?"

"Yes."

"Are there hunters on this planet?"

"No."

"Ah, that is interesting! Are there chickens?"

"No."

"Nothing is perfect, my life is very monotonous...I hunt chickens; men hunt me. All the chickens are just alike, and all the men are just alike. And, in consequence, I am a little bored. But, if you tame me, it will be as if the sun came to shine on my life. I shall know the sound of a step that will be different from all the others. Other steps send me hurrying back underneath the ground. Yours will call me, like music, out of my burrow. And then look: you see the grain-fields down yonder? I do not eat bread. Wheat is of no use to me. The wheat fields have nothing to say to me. And that is sad. But you have hair that is the color of gold. Think how wonderful that will be when you have tamed me! The grain, which is also golden, will bring me back the thought of you. And I shall love to listen to wind in the wheat..."

"Please-- tame me!"

"I want to, very much. But I have not much time. I have friends to discover, and a great many things to understand."

"One only understands the things that one tames. Men have no more time to understand anything. They buy things all ready made at the shops. But there is no shop anywhere where one can buy friendship, and so men have no friends any more. If you want a friend, tame me..."

"what must I do, to tame you?"

"You must be very patient. First you will sit down at a little distance from me-- like that -- in the grass. I shall look at you out of the corner of my eye, and you will say nothing. Words are the source of misunderstandings. But you will sit a little closer to me every day..."

The next day the little prince came back.

"It would have been better to come back at the same hour. If, for example, you come at four o'clock in the afternoon, then at three o'clock I shall begin to be happy. I shall feel happier and happier as the hour advances. At four o'clock, I shall already be worrying and jumping about. I shall show you how happy I am! But if you come at just any time, I shall never know at what hour my heart is to be ready to greet you...One must observe the proper rites..."

"What is a rite?"

"Those also are actions too often neglected. They are what make one day different from other days, one hour from other hours. There is a rite, for example, among my hunters. Every Thursday they dance with the village girls. So Thursday is a wonderful day for me! I can take a walk as far as the vineyards. But if the hunters danced at just any time, every day would be like every other day, and I should never have any vacation at all."

So the little prince tamed the fox. And when the hour of his departure drew near --

"Ah, I shall cry."

"It is your own fault, I never wished you any sort of harm; but you wanted me to tame you... Yes, that is so. Then it has done you no good at all!"

"It has done me good, because of the color of the wheat fields. Go and look again at the roses. You will understand now that yours is unique in all the world. Then come back to say goodbye to me, and I will make you a present of a secret."

The little prince went away, to look again at the roses.

"You are not at all like my rose, As yet you are nothing. No one has tamed you, and you have tamed no one. You are like my fox when I first knew him. He was only a fox like a hundred other foxes. But I have made him my friend, and now he is unique in all the world. You are beautiful, but you are empty. One could not die for you. To be sure, an ordinary passerby would think that my rose looked just like you -- the rose that belongs to me. But in herself alone she is more important than all the hundreds of you other roses: because it is she that I have watered; because it is she that I have put under the glass globe; because it is she that I have sheltered behind the screen; because it is for her that I have killed the caterpillars (except the two or three that we saved to become butterflies); because it is she that I have listened to, when she grumbled, or boasted, or even sometimes when she said nothing. Because she is my rose."

And he went back to meet the fox.

"Goodbye."

"Goodbye."

"And now here is my secret, a very simple secret: It is only with the heart that one can see rightly; what is essential is invisible to the eye. It is the time you have wasted for your rose that makes your rose so important. Men have forgotten this truth, but you must not forget it.  You become responsible, forever, for what you have tamed. You are responsible for your rose..."

"I am responsible for my rose..."

---- Taken from The Little Prince, Antoine de Saint-Exupery.

You Can Be Deeply Passionate Sometimes 
 
You like people, but you're careful about who you get close to. Friendship is important to you... so important that you aren't just friends with anyone.

You fall in love with ease and confidence. Even if you've had bad experiences in the past, each new love is a reason to start completely over.

You are deeply passionate about several things in your life. You're not passionate about much... and the few passions you have are truly obsessions.

Your sense of humor is goofy and silly. You are good at making almost anyone laugh.

I emailed to him the Glory in the flower poem and I also wrote a note in the email (almost the same note in what I posted here in this blog). Here is his reply:

“I read the poem out loud and felt it, too.

We all make imperfect decisions. But sometimes our decisions are shaped by many different factors, and not just our own thinking. Part of growing up is realizing that those decisions were bad and learning from them. The hope is that in our life, we have the chance to learn and to correct the decisions.

The best thing for you and for me is that we both make sure that we make a better life for ourselves and for each other, after all the imperfect decisions we have made. It sounds cliche, but we must continue to strive to be better persons. That's true even for old guys like me.

I'm glad you're moving on. I'm happy you're still letting me be in your life.

I am moving on, but am still figuring out a lot of things. The pain is not there anymore, don't worry about it. There are fears and doubts, but I'm ok.

I will be always here for you, remember that.”


*                    *                       *                  *

I can’t help the tears falling down my cheek. And with the tears is the conviction that I will strive to become a better person and learn to correct the imperfect decisions I made along the way.

(Happy cheers to my next relationship! I can’t wait!). =)

* Niel is kinikilig.

 

(I developed a crush on someone last Sunday while we ate sushi and watched the new James Bond film. And yes, I have been thinking about for the entire week!)

How long will it take for one to heal in a break-up? Any specific formula? A week for every month, a month for every year? Three months? Six months? 

Wisdom from Marc Cherry...

"Nobody takes that long to heal anymore, it's a breakup not a face-lift." - Gabrielle Lange (Episode 75, Art Isn't Easy, Season 4, Desperate Housewives). 

Oh, does that mean I am desperate?! Hehe. =p

I asked Mochi of his opinion of me dating and the possible idea that someone is courting me.

 

He replied positively. He shared his thoughts about it and was generally ok with it. (I am not going to write in detail what he said anymore.)

 

You see, I admit that there are days that I still tread on denial and bargaining. But hearing it from him (again) that I can date and that I can entertain suitors, really means that our romantic relationship is over. His positive opinion about it had a psychological subtraction of denial and bargaining points, and a psychological addition of acceptance points effect on me.

 

Also, last night, I felt (again, psychologically) that a page was turned. A page was flipped. Then there was a blank page on the left side of the book. Then on the right side, I can see a new chapter heading. The chapter heading is not yet written. I, as the author, think that I have to begin a new chapter. I do not know what or how to write it yet.  Time will write itself, I supposed.

 

It is bittersweet. I felt sad that a chapter ended and ended this way. Three years ago, I never thought of this ending for a chapter. But I also feel that I am entitled to feelings of relief, accomplishment, and happiness because I finished writing a chapter.  I even felt celebrating last night and I did. (I went to a Halloween party and got myself tipsy!! J)

 

But for now, I honestly cannot tell how many chapters there are left before this novel ends. But I already have a pretty good idea of what the ending will be.  

 

 

*           *           *           *           *

 

There is something I am very excited about. Another story is currently being written. I am still playing with the concept and the story is still in its exposition stage. I cannot tell if this is a short story or a novel. I only know that I am excited every morning to see how the story unfolds.

 

The leading characters are already named. I named him Dee and he named me El.

"So let me say before we part

So much of me

Is made of what I learned from you

You'll be with me

Like a handprint on my heart

And now whatever way our stories end

I know you have re-written mine

By being my friend.

 

And just to clear the air

I ask forgiveness

For the things I've done you blame me for

 

Who can say if I've been changed for the better?
But because I knew you:

I have been changed for good”

Anger is a natural part of the process of grieving.

 

I never thought that I could be angry at him for this. I thought I do not have the right to be angry since I was the one who committed the mistake. But somehow, during quiet times, when I remember, I feel angry, I feel abandoned.

 

I texted him:

 

September 21, 2008, 7:26 PM

Sometimes, it angers me thinking that you gave up on me.

...to now, Single.

Finally, after a week of space, we talked about our relationship status. And we are stating too many individual differences as our reason. Good talk really. Good ending for the talk too.

We think that there will be a better way for us to relate to one another than lovers... maybe as family. But for now, we will grieve. I will deny. be angry, bargain (or at least last week was all about bargaining), and be depressed. But one day, I will accept and I will be ready to explore and be excited of endless possible new beginnings.

So Mochi, let me sing this one last song (of course, with Bernadetter Peters), our song, my unexpected song.

I cannot seem to change my Friendster status to Single. So I settled for It's Complicated. We are complicated this week. We see each other every day. We talk. And when he is not that conscious, I think he slips and still calls me our endearment terms of each other. Since September 8, I sleep over at his place, but this time I sleep in his study room (I sleep there whenever we are fighting). And everyday I get confused.  

------------------------------------------------------------------

Friends are surprised and sad about it. I am too. I am sorry that I disappointed you too.

------------------------------------------------------------------

Dinner and dessert with Karl, Thursday night.

I told him, "For me, I think it partly failed because i did not ask help from my friends, from you. Not letting you guys know that I was in trouble. It was too late when I started telling you."

He replied, "Nope. It was because you were not ready to end what you were doing."

I was quiet. I disagreed at first. I would have said that it was a struggle. But yes. When I wanted to stop what I was doing, I started telling my friends about it.

*       *       *       * 

Since, it was my first time to eat in that dessert place, I  thought it would be sweet to have a pasalubong and bought him a cake slice. I thought he would like to taste the cake that I ate for dessert too.

And Karl, never missed to say his punch lines, "Honey, it will take more than a cake!"  

I hate you Karl for always telling the truth!

--------------------------------------------------------------

Oh, I decided to stay here in Manila for the second term in La Salle and for the second semester in Ateneo.

--------------------------------------------------------------

So we talked again this evening and the ending? Let me just say that... starting tonight (and hopefully next week), I will have to learn to cope without him. I have to. We need our space to reassess. He needs it. I need it.

-------------------------------------------------------------

Now, I just want to be quiet.
